metadata.title: Influence of Interannual Changes in Ocean Conditions on the Abundance of Walleye Pollock in the Eastern Bering Sea
metadata.description: Time series of anomalies of three month (Jan-Mar) averaged air temperature at St. Paul island, averaged minimum temperature at the bottom layer in the fixed area, distance of 32.0 isohaline from the Alaskan coast and N-W component of wind.
metadata.notes:
Purpose: To examine the influence of winter sea conditions on recruitment of walleye pollock.

Status: In Progress

Maintenance frequency: Annually

Access constraints: FAX and email
